narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Find a project sooner rather than later. Talk to professors as soon as possible.
necessary for the major. choose your instructor/project wisely

I really enjoyed working with Scaz for my senior project. He was full of great insight at all stages of my research, and an excellent person to bounce ideas off of. His extremely busy schedule makes it a little hard to communicate via email, but if you show up to weekly one-on-one meetings with him you should be golden.

yeah i would recommend it. i'd recommend taking it with maybe one other cs course, and try for a holistic goal for the semester -- i took databases, machine learning, and this project (my project was on big data) so it was cool that everything i took was related in some way. you can do as much or as little as you want pretty much for the thesis. build a relationship with your advisor and you'll have a good time
